# ─── Firebase Configuration ─────────────────────────────────────────
# These variables are required for cross-device data sync via Firebase
# Realtime Database.  When omitted, the app runs in local-only mode
# (data stored in browser localStorage only).
#
# 1. Create a Firebase project at https://console.firebase.google.com
# 2. Enable Realtime Database (region: asia-southeast1)
# 3. Enable Authentication > Anonymous sign-in + Email/Password sign-in
# 4. Create an admin user in Authentication > Users
# 5. Set RTDB rules: .write to "auth.provider === 'password'"
# 6. Copy your config values below
#
# For GitHub Pages deployment, add these as repository secrets and
# reference them in .github/workflows/deploy.yml.

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
